{
  "texts": [
    "If successful, our approach could enable a new wave of practical LLM applications in these domains, unlocking capabilities where training signals were previously scarce or unreliable.",
    "This would allow for the deployment of robust reasoning systems in complex, real-world environments without the need for expensive or impossible-to-design verifiers.",
    "Here we describe the specific techniques that enable stable and efficient learning in RARO.",
    "Shared LLM for Critic and Policy.",
    "While Algorithm 1 provides a practical procedure for alternating updates of the policy (θ) and the critic model (ϕ) it requires training two reasoning LLMs and thus incurs long, token-intensive rollouts for both."
  ]
}